key_insights: Tesla's FSD (Full Self-Driving) has undergone significant architectural changes with V12, moving to a neural network-based, almost entirely AI-driven approach.
Numerous FSD software updates are being rapidly rolled out, including versions V12.5.6.1, V13, V13.2, V13.3, and V14, with V14 being described as the second biggest update after V12.

Key new and upcoming features include end-to-end highway driving (already shipped to ~50k customers for AI4 vehicles), 'Actually Smart Summon', dynamic road-closure routing, autonomous parking, eye-tracking technology, and improvements in highway speed and vehicle follow distance. The roadmap also mentions 'Reverse in FSD'.
